.TH AUH 1 "November 2025" "auh 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
auh \- Arch User Helper for AUR package management
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B auh
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ packages... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B auh
(Arch User Helper) is a modern, lightweight AUR helper designed for Arch Linux. It provides a simple command-line interface for managing AUR packages with minimal dependencies and fast compile times.
.PP
The tool features automatic fallback to GitHub mirrors when the AUR is unavailable, parallel package installation for improved performance, and an APT-like command interface with getopts support for ease of use.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B install
Install packages from AUR. Automatically falls back to GitHub mirror if AUR is down.
.TP
.B remove
Remove installed packages.
.TP
.B update
Update packages. If no package is specified, performs a full system upgrade.
.TP
.B clean
Clean the package cache.
.TP
.B sync
List explicitly installed packages that are available in AUR.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Install Options
.TP
.BR \-g ", " \-\-github
Install packages directly from GitHub mirror instead of AUR.
.SS Remove Options
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-autoremove
Also remove dependencies that are not required by other packages (pacman -Rsn instead of -R).
.SS Package Arguments
.TP
.I packages...
One or more package names to process. Package names should contain only alphanumeric characters, dashes, underscores, dots, and plus signs.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B auh install yay
Install the 'yay' package from AUR.
.TP
.B auh install yay pikaur
Install multiple packages in parallel.
.TP
.B auh install \-g package-name
Install a package directly from GitHub mirror using the -g flag.
.TP
.B auh install \-\-github package-name
Install a package directly from GitHub mirror using the --github flag.
.TP
.B auh remove yay
Remove the 'yay' package (uses pacman -R).
.TP
.B auh remove \-s yay
Remove the 'yay' package and its dependencies (uses pacman -Rsn).
.TP
.B auh remove \-\-autoremove yay
Remove the 'yay' package and its dependencies using the long option form.
.TP
.B auh update
Perform a full system upgrade.
.TP
.B auh update package-name
Update a specific package.
.TP
.B auh clean
Clean the package cache.
.TP
.B auh sync
List explicitly installed AUR packages.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.B auh
requires the following dependencies:
.IP \[bu] 2
.B curl
\- for downloading data from AUR and GitHub
.IP \[bu]
.B git
\- for cloning package repositories
.IP \[bu]
.B jq
\- for JSON parsing
.IP \[bu]
.B base-devel
\- for building packages (includes makepkg)
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /tmp/auh_*
Temporary directories used for building and updating packages.
.TP
.I /tmp/auh_mirror_*
Temporary directories used when installing from GitHub mirrors.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.B auh
uses the following system tools and respects their environment variables:
.IP \[bu] 2
.BR pacman (8)
.IP \[bu]
.BR makepkg (8)
.IP \[bu]
.BR git (1)
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error (invalid command, package not found, build failure, etc.)
.TP
.B 4
Build failure when installing from GitHub mirror
.SH SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS
.IP \[bu] 2
Always review PKGBUILDs before installing packages from AUR
.IP \[bu]
The tool requires sudo privileges for certain operations
.IP \[bu]
Package names are validated to prevent command injection
.IP \[bu]
Network operations use HTTPS for secure communication
